Hello,

Content-encoding has to do with compression, not character encoding. See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_compression

Recorder.getReplayInputStream() returns the raw binary data from the server, including http headers, possibly chunked

Recorder.getContentReplayInputStream() returns the un-chunked, un-content-encoded payload (no http headers). If you want the raw content this is probably the one to use. It basically corresponds what e.g. wget would save to disk.

Recorder.getContentReplayCharSequence() returns getContentReplayInputStream() interpreted as text according to getCharset(). The charset is a best guess which can be adjusted over the course of processing (see ExtractorHTML.innerExtract() for example).

Noah


